-- Turkey's Finansbank looks into possible secondary public offering 
-- 
-- Fri Sep 19, 2014 03:33AM EDT
-- None



ISTANBUL, Sept 19 (Reuters) - Turkey's Finansbank <FINBN.IS>, which is owned by National Bank of Greece <NBGr.AT>, said on Friday it had begun work on a possible secondary public offering of its shares.

It said in a statement to the Istanbul stock exchange that it planned to mandate investment banks and brokerages on the subject in the coming period.